tree-borne seed oils in this study showed various fatty acid
compositions. Some seed oils had a high level of medium-
chain fatty acids, others had a high level of monounsaturated
fatty acids, and yet others had a high level of polyunsaturated
fatty acids. Although polyunsaturated fatty acids are known
to function as various biological membranes and are in-
volved in cell metabolism, the human body often fails to
synthesize suﬃcient amounts; therefore, such deﬁciency
needs to be supplemented by an external source (food) [28].
